(146, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2013/02/have-a-virtual-meeting/'' title=''I was interviewed by Fast Company on How To Have A Virtual Meeting, which they turned into a neat article. [&hellip;]''>Matt: Have A Virtual Meeting</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/KOWt3nOP2hQ/'' title=''There’s no denying it, WordPress is a big thing, so are WordCamps, and 2012 was bigger and better than ever for the popular WordPress conferences! There were a total of 67 WordCamps this year, up from 52 last year, with 34 in the US and 33 outside of the US, serving over 17,000 attendees, with 967 sessions and 877 speakers, all made possible by 498 generous  [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: WordCamp 2012 Roundup</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://blackberry.wordpress.org/2013/02/05/version-2-2-6/'' title=''Version 2.2.6 of WordPress for BlackBerry 10 and PlayBook is now available on the BlackBerry World. What’s New? The number one priority is to make the app more stable, and WordPress for BlackBerry now runs beautifully on both BlackBerry 10 devices and the PlayBook. Improved support for connecting over HTTPS. Stability improvements. We continue to make the ap [&hellip;]''>WP Blackberry: Version 2.2.6 Now Available for BlackBerry 10 and PlayBook</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ios.wordpress.org/2013/02/04/version-3-4/'' title=''Need to get your WordPress.com notifications on the go? With version 3.4 of WordPress for iOS you’ll see all your WordPress.com and Jetpack blog Notifications right on your iPhone, iPad, or iPod Touch. Notifications With the new streamlined Notifications view, you can step away from your computer but still stay connected to your readers. With just a few taps [&hellip;]''>WP iPhone: Version 3.4 Keeps You In the Loop: Introducing Notifications</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2013/02/dont/'' title=''Michael Mulvey writes “My advice to designers in need of portfolio pieces and jobs is to not do three things: Wait, Ask For Permission and Stop.” [&hellip;]''>Matt: Don’t</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
